  <div xmlns:v="http://rdf.data-vocabulary.org/#" typeof="v:Review">
    <div class="main review-item" id="5437146">
        

  <header class="main-hd">
    <h3 class="title">
      <a href="https://book.douban.com/review/5437146/" class="title-link">总体来说还行</a>
      <div class="toggle_review right">        <a href="javascript:;" id="toggle-5437146"class="indicator unfold j" title="展开全文">        </a>
      </div>
    </h3>
    

<div class="header-more">
    <a class="author-avatar" href="https://www.douban.com/people/60884927/"><img width="48" height="48" src="https://img3.doubanio.com/icon/u60884927-2.jpg"></a>
    <a href="https://www.douban.com/people/60884927/" class="author">
      <span property="v:reviewer">静音的FM</span>
    </a>    <span property="v:rating" class="allstar40 main-title-rating" title="推荐"></span>
  <span property="v:dtreviewed" content="2012-05-21"
      class="main-meta">2012-05-21 23:09:23</span>
</div>

  </header>

        <div class="main-bd">
          <div id="review_5437146_short" class="review-short">
            <div class="short-content">
                  很同意一个豆友的说法，叫北非战记更为合适，讲了很多关于二战的背景故事，如果对欧洲历史不太清楚的，看了这本书倒是可以懂个入门。感觉在这本书里面，隆美尔本人的个性还是不够突出，但是从故事的角度来欣赏，就还行吧。

                  <div class="more-info pl clearfix">
                    <span class="left">0有用 / 0没用</span>
